Package: CausalSurvival
Title: Causal Inference for Single-Event Survival Outcomes
Version: 0.1.3
Authors@R: c(
    person("Alex", "Mourer", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "MourerAlex@users.noreply.github.com")
    )
Description: Discrete-time pooled logistic regression estimators for causal
    survival analysis with a single failure event and right censoring.
    Implements the parametric g-formula (plug-in) and inverse probability
    weighting (IPW) for cumulative incidence under static, baseline-only
    treatment regimes, following Hernán and Robins (Causal Inference: What
    If). Provides bootstrap percentile confidence intervals, identifying
    assumption accessors, and weight diagnostics. Designed as the foundation
    of a two-package ecosystem with CausalCompetingRisks, which extends to
    competing events via the separable-effects framework.
